{
  "texts": [
    "Research in adaptive learning seeks to optimize the learning journey by tailoring content, pace, and assessments to individual students' abilities, ultimately improving educational outcomes (Rane et al., 2023. Based on the capabilities of current state-of-the-art ChatGPT, two primary forms of adaptivity are employed to enhance conversations with tutor bots for learning: content adaptation and feedback customization.",
    "Content adaptation involves tailoring the information presented to meet the individual learner's needs, ensuring that the material is relevant and comprehensible (Park & Lee, 2013).",
    "Feedback customization refers to the ability of the chatbot to provide personalized responses and suggestions based on the learner's performance and queries (Huang et al., 2022; Kuhail et al., 2023).",
    "These adaptive features contribute to claims of personalized and positive learning outcomes.",
    "As LLMs continue to develop at a fast pace, research is needed to understand how LLMs can be further designed or trained to provide more sustained and authentic PL (Kabir & Lin, 2023; Nascimento et al., 2023; Zhuang et al., 2023)."
  ]
}